    <h4 class="mb-3" style="color: #ba55d3; font-weight: 600;">🧴 Understanding Skin Types & Recommended Products</h4>
    <p><strong>Dry Skin:</strong> Often feels tight and may flake. Use hydrating cleansers, thick moisturizers (like creams with hyaluronic acid), and nourishing serums.</p>
    <p><strong>Oily Skin:</strong> Prone to shine and breakouts. Use foaming cleansers, oil-free moisturizers, and products with salicylic acid or niacinamide.</p>
    <p><strong>Combination Skin:</strong> Oily in the T-zone, dry elsewhere. Use balancing toners and light moisturizers; treat zones separately.</p>
    <p><strong>Sensitive Skin:</strong> Easily irritated. Choose fragrance-free, hypoallergenic products, and soothing ingredients like aloe or chamomile.</p>
    <p><strong>Normal Skin:</strong> Balanced, few issues. Maintain with gentle cleansers, lightweight moisturizer, and SPF.</p>
    <p class="text-muted mt-3">💡 Tip: Always patch-test new products and adjust your routine to the season.</p>
